Buddha bowl video link https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=10154965298957437

2x cubed sweet potatos
2 x sliced red onions
2 x chicken breasts
2 tsps garlic powder
2 tsps ginger powder
2 portions of cooked brown rice
2 handfuls of baby spinach

For the dressing:
1/2 cup peanut butter - preferably x brand
1 tbsp local sourced honey
2 tbsp soy sauce
1/2 cup lime juice
4 cloves of garlic
1/2 cup olive oil
1 tbsp sesame oil

1) preheat the oven to 200c
2) place the sweet potato and red onion on a baking sheet, coast with olive oil and season with salt and pepper
3) Roast for 35 mins in the oven
4) lay the chicken breasts on a plate or board. sprinkle both sides with garlic and ginger powder. Season on both sides
5) Add olive oil to a pan over medium flame, cook the chicken breasts for 6 mins on each side
6) For the dressing add all of the ingredients to a small bowl and mix throughly, season to taste
7) Assemble your bowl! Rice as the base, then add the veg, cut up chicken, spinach and dressign over the top!

3 tin dahl https://www.tinnedtomatoes.com/2017/05/three-tin-tomato-turmeric-coconut-dahl.html

300g brown rice
1 tbsp coconut oil
1 tbsp olive oil
2 tsp cumin
2 tsp turmeric
1 tsp ground coriander
1 x 300g tin green lentils, drained and rinsed
1 x 400g tin chopped tomatoes
1 x 400ml tin coconut milk
a good grinding of salt and pepper
2 tbsp fresh coriander, finely chopped
140g kale, chopped

1. Boil your rice in a pan over a medium heat until it is soft but still has a little bite. Check out the packet instructions.
2. Now make the dahl. Place the oil and coconut oil in a large pan and heat for 1 minute, then add the spices and cook for a minute or two until golden. Add the drained lentils along with the coconut milk and tomatoes, then cover. Cooke for 20 minutes or until slightly reduced. Stir regularly and add a little water, if you think it needs it.
3. Remove from the heat, season with salt and pepper and add the fresh coriander.
4. Serve with the rice and lightly cooked kale.
5. Enjoy!

Feta n grains https://elizabethchloe.com/roasted-vegetables-feta-and-grains/

1 aubergine, in 1cm slices
1 courgette, in 1cm slices
1 red pepper, in 1cm slices
2 tbsp olive oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp pepper
2 tsp dried oregano
200g cherry tomatoes
1 sachet of Merchant Gourmet Glorious Grains
Juice of 1 lemon
100g feta cheese
50g pine nuts

1) Heat your oven up to 180Âºc.
2) Toss the aubergine, courgette and red pepper with the olive oil, salt, pepper and oregano. Spread the vegetables out evenly in a baking tray and pop in the oven for 20 minutes.
3) Remove the vegetables from the oven, add in the cherry tomatoes and toss everything together.
4) Return the dish to the oven for another 15 minutes.
5) After 15 minutes add the Merchant Gourmet Glorious Grains and lemon juice to the roasting dish and mix them in with the roast vegetables. Sprinkle the feta and pine nuts on top and return the pan to the oven for a final 5 minutes to warm everything through. Serve up and enjoy!


